<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-493-868  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 493 868.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Systems News  August 7 1989 n429 p4(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>McDonnell Douglas in hardware retreat.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Moore, John.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>To underscore its commitment to systems integration, the McDonnellDouglas Corp has announced its planned divestment of two of itsinformation systems businesses.andP;  The two are: its Network Systemsunit, including the Tymnet public data network, to be sold toBritish Telecom PLC for $355 million; and its Computer SystemsInc, to be merged with its Information Systems International andrestructured as a UK public company.andP;  McDonnell Douglas' SystemsIntegration division earned $229 million in 1988 and ranked secondamong aerospace manufacturers.andP;  Within a twelve-month period, thecompany has won three multiyear, multimillion-dollar systemsintegration contracts from the Massachusetts' Dept of EnvironmentResources; from a similar Pennsylvania agency; and from Trane Coof LaCrosse, WI.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   McDonnell Douglas Corp. (divestment)Tymnet-McDonnell Douglas Network Systems Co. (acquisitions andmergers).andO;Ticker:    NSCO; MD.andO;Topic:     Computer Systems IntegratorsDivestmentInformation SystemsReorganization.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>